comments: Fox (SAC) and Davis (LAL) engage and disengage with one another as they each attempt to establish post position.
Prince (LAL) avoids stepping out of bounds as he starts his dribble.
Huerter (SAC) brings his left hand toward Davis' (LAL) side and marginal contact occurs as the ball falls overhead during the rebound.
Vincent (LAL) establishes himself in Murray's (SAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Fox (SAC) moves somewhat laterally prior to marginal body contact occurring with James (LAL) along the sideline.
James (LAL) goes to, not through, Fox (SAC) and spins off of the marginal body contact that occurs as they come together along the sideline.
Barnes (SAC) legally contests Russell's (LAL) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Vincent (LAL) and Fox (SAC) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs as the screen approaches.
Barnes (SAC) establishes himself in Vincent's (LAL) path and turns slightly prior to marginal contact occurring as the screen is set.
Barnes (SAC) firms up over his left foot after the hand-off and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the pick on Prince (LAL).
Russell (LAL) and Barnes (SAC) each make clean contact with the ball as they pursue the rebound.
Huerter (SAC) moves laterally into Russell's (LAL) path and initiates body contact that affects Russell's SQBR in transition.
Vincent (LAL) legally contests Fox's (SAC) jump shot attempt.

Prince (LAL) and Huerter (SAC) come together at the same spot after the release of the jump shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs. Prince and Huerter then briefly engage and disengage with one another, and further marginal contact occurs as the ball ricochets off of the backboard.
Barnes (SAC) moves forward slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Russell (LAL) as Russell cuts back toward him in transition.
Murray (SAC) attempts to establish himself in Prince's (LAL) path and as Prince slips by to Murray's side, marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Huerter (SAC) brushes Davis' (LAL) left arm and marginal contact occurs as Davis finishes at the rim during the put-back.
Vincent (LAL) extends his right arm into Fox's (SAC) path and initiates contact to Fox's front in transition.
Murray (SAC) brings both hands forward prior to marginal contact occurring with James' (LAL) side during the drive.
Davis (LAL) and Barnes (SAC) mutually engage and disengage with one another as they each attempt to establish position in the lane.
Murray (SAC) legally contests James' (LAL) driving shot attempt.
Vincent (LAL) brings his right arm forward as he attempts to dislodge the ball and marginal contact occurs with Fox's (SAC) side prior to the start of Fox's dribble.
Davis (LAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.

McGee's (SAC) left arm comes up toward Davis' (LAL) left shoulder/neck area and marginal contact occurs prior to McGee disengaging during the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Davis (LAL) brushes Huerter's (SAC) arm and marginal contact occurs as Huerter secures the rebound.
McGee's (SAC) momentum carries him to the floor and incidental contact occurs with Davis (LAL) as Davis moves forward toward McGee in an attempt to secure the rebound.
Murray (SAC) and Prince (LAL) jump toward one another as they each pursue the rebound and incidental body contact occurs when they come together in the air.
James (LAL) establishes himself in Huerter's (SAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Huerter (SAC) brings his right hand toward Russell's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs with Russell's front as he drives toward the lane.
Murray (SAC) re-establishes his defensive position after Russell (LAL) plants to elevate and marginal contact occurs when they come together as Russell returns to the floor.
McGee (SAC) establishes himself in Vincent's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Davis (LAL) brings his hands forward prior to marginal contact occurring with Monk's (SAC) front/side during the drive.
Vincent (LAL) brings his right arm toward McGee's (SAC) side and marginal contact occurs as McGee elevates for the rebound.
Vincent (LAL) establishes himself in Barnes' (SAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Russell (LAL) moves somewhat laterally prior to marginal body contact occurring with Monk (SAC) along the sideline.
James (LAL) initiates contact across Monk's (SAC) right arm along the sideline.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: James (LAL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Vincent (LAL) commits a take foul on Monk (SAC).
Prince (LAL) briefly has his arms around Vezenkov's (SAC) upper half before correcting.

Russell (LAL) makes incidental contact with Barnes' (SAC) face while cutting to get open during the inbound.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
